TWO suspects aged 24 and 39 were bust by the Hawks on Thursday, 10 February. They face charges of fraud, theft and contravention of the Cybercrime Act after being in possession and presenting a fake card at Veritas petrol station in Middelburg, Mpumalanga. Captain Dineo Sekgotodi said its alleged on 9 February, the two poured petrol at the petrol station and submitted a fake bank card to pay and left. “It was later discovered the card was fraudulent. The case was opened for investigation. On Thursday, 10 February, the bank investigator went to the filling station to question about the fraudulent transaction and that is when the attendant saw the vehicle which poured petrol the previous day,” Sekgotodi said. She said the attendant informed the investigating officer after the vehicle was spotted and the Hawks came and arrested the two. “The accused appeared in the Middelburg Magistrates Court and were held in custody. The case was postponed to Friday, 18 February for confirmation of their addresses,” said Sekgotodi.